我其实是来采访辛西娅·德里斯科尔的
I'm actually supposed to do an interview with Cynthia Driscoll.

398
00:29:27,160 --> 00:29:29,250
先遣人员叫我来这边
The Advance guys said I should come this way.

399
00:29:31,030 --> 00:29:31,920
在这里等一下
Wait here.

400
00:29:41,730 --> 00:29:45,000
抱歉  总统先生  我们做不到
I'm sorry, Mr. President, we just can't do it.

401
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:47,800
这里45%的选票在非裔手中
Forty-five percent of the vote here is African American.

402
00:29:47,800 --> 00:29:49,740
你和你母亲对我的支持
You and your mother standing by my side

403
00:29:49,740 --> 00:29:51,270
会有很重要的作用...
would go a long way to put this--

404
00:29:51,270 --> 00:29:54,850
我在一个非裔及拉丁裔的选区竞选议员
I am running for Congress in a black and Latino district.

405
00:29:55,060 --> 00:29:58,610
我母亲曾在游行时被暴打  被水冲
My mother was beaten and hosed down in marches.

406
00:29:58,610 --> 00:30:02,110
你想让我们替一个三K党人的儿子作担保吗
You want us to vouch for a man whose father was in the KKK?

407
00:30:02,120 --> 00:30:05,250
-不  他不是三K党  -照片上那个就是他
- No, he was not in the Klan. - That was him in that picture.

408
00:30:05,250 --> 00:30:06,670
对  可这个我已经解释过了
Yes, but I've explained that.

409
00:30:06,670 --> 00:30:08,730
内战就是在本州掀起的
This is the state where the Civil War started,

410
00:30:08,730 --> 00:30:10,990
有些人汽车保险杠上还贴着南军旗贴纸
where you can still see rebel flags on bumper stickers.

411
00:30:10,990 --> 00:30:14,890
这里曾有很严重的种族暴行  总统先生
There is a history of racist brutality here, Mr. President.

412
00:30:15,500 --> 00:30:17,880
那种形象影响很大
Those sort of symbols matter.

413
00:30:18,270 --> 00:30:20,130
能让你母亲接电话吗
Could you put your mother on, please?

414
00:30:23,380 --> 00:30:24,290
妈妈
Mom?

415
00:30:24,650 --> 00:30:25,780
他想跟你说话
He wants to speak to you.

416
00:30:30,510 --> 00:30:31,640
总统先生
Mr. President.

417
00:30:31,770 --> 00:30:35,360
听着  我们需要团结  我替西莉娅背书了
Listen, we need to stand together. Now, I've endorsed Celia.

418
00:30:35,360 --> 00:30:37,800
克莱尔在德州能给她帮很大忙
Claire can do a great deal for her in Texas.

419
00:30:37,840 --> 00:30:41,170
现在远离安德伍德一家对她更好
She's better off without the Underwoods at this point.

420
00:30:41,170 --> 00:30:42,610
那你的诊所呢
But what about your clinic?

421
00:30:42,610 --> 00:30:45,960
你要是拿我们的诊所要挟我  别人会怎么看
Imagine how that would look, holding our clinic for ransom.

422
00:30:46,010 --> 00:30:49,110
我是想博取您的友好  议员女士
I'm appealing to your goodwill, Congresswoman.

423
00:30:49,400 --> 00:30:52,970
等我们不再遭受殴打和枪击
When we stop getting beaten and shot...

424
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:56,420
我就会对您友好的  总统先生
you'll have my goodwill, Mr. President.

425
00:30:57,310 --> 00:30:58,280
再见
Goodbye.

426
